Qing'e.

276
00:17:45,560 --> 00:17:47,080
Qing'e, come out. Look who's back.

277
00:17:48,400 --> 00:17:49,760
Look, hurry, look.

278
00:18:14,200 --> 00:18:15,440
Why are you living here?

279
00:18:22,000 --> 00:18:23,280
How can anyone live here?

280
00:18:26,840 --> 00:18:28,880
Those people must've bullied you.

281
00:18:33,560 --> 00:18:35,040
They must be bullying you.

282
00:18:37,000 --> 00:18:38,160
How can anyone live here?

283
00:18:43,320 --> 00:18:44,520
This place is so terrible.

284
00:18:52,080 --> 00:18:54,440
Tell me who bullied you.

285
00:18:54,920 --> 00:18:56,520
Those jerks. I'll go sort them out.

286
00:18:56,620 --> 00:18:59,100
(Hot water)

287
00:18:59,120 --> 00:19:00,800
No one's bullying me.

288
00:19:02,160 --> 00:19:03,520
I'm really fine, Uncle.

289
00:19:03,520 --> 00:19:04,480
I'm doing great.

290
00:19:04,480 --> 00:19:05,840
Who was it? Tell me.

291
00:19:06,400 --> 00:19:08,320
Look, I'm doing just fine.

292
00:19:09,440 --> 00:19:10,280
Well...

293
00:19:12,600 --> 00:19:13,760
How can you live here?

294
00:19:16,400 --> 00:19:17,240
This place...

295
00:19:19,400 --> 00:19:20,720
It's okay, Uncle.

296
00:19:40,640 --> 00:19:42,320
I did well in there,

297
00:19:43,560 --> 00:19:44,600
so they cut my time short

298
00:19:45,480 --> 00:19:47,120
and let me out early.

299
00:19:49,520 --> 00:19:50,400
That's good.

300
00:19:53,840 --> 00:19:55,320
Qin Bawa went to see me.

301
00:19:56,920 --> 00:19:59,640
I know a bit about your situation.

302
00:20:01,680 --> 00:20:03,800
Qing'e, it must've been hard on you.

303
00:20:04,200 --> 00:20:05,280
It's nothing.

304
00:20:10,960 --> 00:20:12,560
You can perform opera now.

305
00:20:13,320 --> 00:20:14,720
And you sing so well.

306
00:20:16,320 --> 00:20:17,760
I never saw that coming.

307
00:20:19,240 --> 00:20:21,240
My masters taught me well.

308
00:20:25,800 --> 00:20:27,720
I owe them more than I can repay.

309
00:20:29,640 --> 00:20:30,840
I have to pay it back.

310
00:21:25,920 --> 00:21:26,760
Uncle,

311
00:21:27,440 --> 00:21:28,760
can you come back to the troupe?

312
00:21:31,000 --> 00:21:31,840
I don't know.

313
00:21:46,800 --> 00:21:47,640
Who are you here for?

314
00:21:51,640 --> 00:21:52,680
Hu Sanyuan.

315
00:21:54,760 --> 00:21:55,600
Sit.

316
00:21:56,880 --> 00:21:58,720
I heard you were back two days ago.

317
00:21:58,720 --> 00:21:59,840
The police told me

318
00:21:59,840 --> 00:22:01,080
you behaved well in there,

319
00:22:01,080 --> 00:22:02,600
so you got out early.

320
00:22:03,200 --> 00:22:04,040
Sit down.

321
00:22:07,640 --> 00:22:09,200
I've waited for two days for you.

322
00:22:10,600 --> 00:22:12,400
I went to Nail's hometown

323
00:22:12,400 --> 00:22:13,640
and apologized to his parents.

324
00:22:14,120 --> 00:22:16,400
I burned paper at Nail's grave.

325
00:22:18,240 --> 00:22:20,480
Welcome back to society.

326
00:22:25,000 --> 00:22:25,840
You've lost weight.

327
00:22:26,080 --> 00:22:27,440
In there,

328
00:22:27,440 --> 00:22:28,280
was it hard?

329
00:22:28,920 --> 00:22:29,760
Not really.

330
00:22:31,240 --> 00:22:33,080
How was the food? Was it enough?

331
00:22:33,080 --> 00:22:33,920
Yeah.

332
00:22:34,240 --> 00:22:35,880
Did anyone give you trouble in there?

333
00:22:36,720 --> 00:22:37,560
Not for me.

334
00:22:38,640 --> 00:22:39,720
I knew it.

335
00:22:39,720 --> 00:22:41,720
You can survive anywhere.

336
00:22:42,440 --> 00:22:43,280
Troupe Leader,

337
00:22:43,440 --> 00:22:44,666
I want to return to the troupe.

338
00:22:47,520 --> 00:22:49,160
I hope you return too.

339
00:22:49,560 --> 00:22:51,040
Personal ties aside,

340
00:22:52,040 --> 00:22:53,240
the troupe needs you.

341
00:22:53,506 --> 00:22:54,840
The orchestra needs you even more.

342
00:22:56,880 --> 00:22:57,840
But you have no idea.

343
00:22:57,840 --> 00:22:58,920
After you were caught,

344
00:22:58,920 --> 00:23:00,640
Huang Zhengjing dismissed you.

345
00:23:01,520 --> 00:23:04,000
If we restore your status right now,

346
00:23:04,920 --> 00:23:05,880
that's just impossible.

347
00:23:06,600 --> 00:23:08,080
Letting you back into the orchestra

348
00:23:08,440 --> 00:23:09,600
is even more impossible.

349
00:23:10,280 --> 00:23:11,280
I hope you understand.

350
00:23:12,640 --> 00:23:13,480
I understand.

351
00:23:15,800 --> 00:23:16,640
Here's the thing.

352
00:23:17,120 --> 00:23:20,440
I wanted to start you
as a temporary worker,

353
00:23:20,800 --> 00:23:22,000
helping out in our kitchen,

354
00:23:22,720 --> 00:23:24,240
but now, the kid...

355
00:23:24,640 --> 00:23:25,760
Things are different now.

356
00:23:26,040 --> 00:23:27,400
It's not like it used to be.

357
00:23:28,000 --> 00:23:30,080
She's our leading performer now.

358
00:23:30,760 --> 00:23:32,560
She's vital to our troupe.

359
00:23:33,440 --> 00:23:34,960
What happened back then

360
00:23:35,760 --> 00:23:38,040
hit her really hard.

361
00:23:39,160 --> 00:23:41,600
If you come back now,

362
00:23:41,920 --> 00:23:43,560
I'm worried

363
00:23:43,560 --> 00:23:45,960
that her hard-won confidence

364
00:23:46,600 --> 00:23:47,880
could be shattered again.

365
00:23:51,920 --> 00:23:52,800
You're right.

366
00:24:06,920 --> 00:24:07,760
Okay, okay.

367
00:24:08,080 --> 00:24:08,920
Eat up.

368
00:24:09,240 --> 00:24:11,160
Go on, eat some more.

369
00:24:18,040 --> 00:24:19,640
They don't want you back?

370
00:24:22,160 --> 00:24:23,360
I changed my mind.

371
00:24:23,760 --> 00:24:24,706
I don't want to go back.

372
00:24:24,840 --> 00:24:25,680
Why?

373
00:24:29,040 --> 00:24:30,680
When you first joined the troupe,

374
00:24:30,680 --> 00:24:31,520
you said

375
00:24:32,480 --> 00:24:34,120
that the troupe was like a sheep pen.

376
00:24:35,520 --> 00:24:36,600
I don't remember.

377
00:24:38,120 --> 00:24:39,040
I didn't see it then.

378
00:24:40,600 --> 00:24:42,680
Now, I think you had a point.

379
00:24:44,400 --> 00:24:46,280
I don't want to be penned in there.

380
00:24:48,360 --> 00:24:49,600
Then, what will you do?

381
00:24:50,120 --> 00:24:51,360
Don't worry about me.

382
00:24:52,360 --> 00:24:53,280
I'll be fine.

383
00:24:54,720 --> 00:24:55,960
I'll live well.

384
00:24:56,560 --> 00:24:57,600
Just in a different way.

385
00:25:15,000 --> 00:25:15,840
What are you doing?

386
00:25:20,459 --> 00:25:21,688
Take it back. I don't want it.

387
00:25:21,760 --> 00:25:22,720
Keep it.

388
00:25:25,480 --> 00:25:26,720
You send money home every month?

389
00:25:46,840 --> 00:25:47,880
Consider it a loan to me.

390
00:25:48,640 --> 00:25:49,480
I'll pay you back.

391
00:26:21,020 --> 00:26:28,020
(Restaurant; Ningzhou specialties,
Northern and Southern cuisine)

392
00:26:28,080 --> 00:26:29,080
All right. Go back.

393
00:26:31,440 --> 00:26:32,880
Don't worry about me. Bye.

394
00:26:38,060 --> 00:26:40,780
(Restaurant)

395
00:26:40,780 --> 00:26:43,820
(Department Store)

396
00:27:34,760 --> 00:27:38,450
ظآزI came down from the mountainsظآز

397
00:27:38,450 --> 00:27:41,300
ظآزCarrying orchid grassظآز

398
00:27:42,120 --> 00:27:45,570
ظآزI planted it in my little gardenظآز

399
00:27:45,570 --> 00:27:48,950
ظآزHoping it would bloom soonظآز

400
00:27:49,480 --> 00:27:53,170
ظآزI checked on it three times a dayظآز

401
00:27:53,170 --> 00:27:56,210
ظآزWatching it as the days went byظآز

402
00:28:34,380 --> 00:28:35,560
(Yunnan Baiyao, Mercurochrome)

403
00:28:35,560 --> 00:28:37,160
Take these two bottles.

404
00:28:37,400 --> 00:28:38,960
Use some wherever you're hurt.

405
00:28:39,560 --> 00:28:40,480
Thanks.

406
00:28:41,800 --> 00:28:42,720
Where's your uncle?

407
00:28:43,680 --> 00:28:44,520
He left.

408
00:28:44,920 --> 00:28:45,760
Left?

409
00:28:46,200 --> 00:28:47,280
Where did he go?

410
00:28:47,560 --> 00:28:48,400
I don't know.

411
00:28:49,680 --> 00:28:51,400
Why leave right after coming back?

412
00:29:11,400 --> 00:29:12,840
I was thinking

413
00:29:14,480 --> 00:29:15,680
that maybe he could play drums

414
00:29:15,680 --> 00:29:17,360
for us for the show.

415
00:29:20,280 --> 00:29:22,440
He brought me here, but he left.

416
00:29:25,360 --> 00:29:26,360
So, all these years,

417
00:29:27,520 --> 00:29:28,720
have you missed your uncle?

418
00:29:29,880 --> 00:29:30,720
I don't know.

419
00:29:32,880 --> 00:29:34,280
How can you not know?

420
00:29:34,840 --> 00:29:36,280
I just don't know.

421
00:29:38,880 --> 00:29:40,320
When your uncle left,

422
00:29:41,160 --> 00:29:42,400
were you upset?

423
00:29:45,600 --> 00:29:46,640
No.

424
00:29:47,240 --> 00:29:48,600
Why?

425
00:29:51,560 --> 00:29:52,760
Somehow,

426
00:29:53,680 --> 00:29:56,320
he felt like a stranger to me.

427
00:29:58,240 --> 00:30:00,200
He must've felt the same way.

428
00:30:00,480 --> 00:30:02,480
He doesn't know what to say to me.

429
00:30:03,880 --> 00:30:05,480
Maybe that's why he left.

430
00:30:11,520 --> 00:30:12,360
Then,

431
00:30:15,080 --> 00:30:16,680
do I feel like a stranger to you?

432
00:30:29,900 --> 00:30:31,060
(Yunnan Baiyao, Mercurochrome)

433
00:30:33,760 --> 00:30:35,160
You should get some sleep, too.

434
00:31:20,753 --> 00:31:21,839
What happened to your head?

435
00:31:32,480 --> 00:31:33,720
Why are you looking at me?

436
00:31:34,440 --> 00:31:35,480
You think I did it?

437
00:31:36,400 --> 00:31:37,360
I fell on my own.

438
00:31:37,640 --> 00:31:38,480
Really?

439
00:31:39,090 --> 00:31:41,160
- It doesn't look like it.
- I told you.

440
00:31:41,240 --> 00:31:42,520
He said he fell.

441
00:31:43,240 --> 00:31:44,080
How would I know?

442
00:31:44,440 --> 00:31:45,280
Right, right.

443
00:31:47,640 --> 00:31:49,640
Do you still want to be in this play?

444
00:31:50,800 --> 00:31:51,640
Yes.

445
00:31:52,680 --> 00:31:55,360
Fall again, and you're out.

446
00:31:56,960 --> 00:31:57,800
Okay.

447
00:32:06,200 --> 00:32:07,840
Especially around the warehouse.

448
00:32:08,240 --> 00:32:09,760
It's a key fire-safety area.

449
00:32:10,280 --> 00:32:12,000
Check for aging wiring.

450
00:32:12,250 --> 00:32:13,530
- Inspect it.
- Director Huang.

451
00:32:14,640 --> 00:32:16,360
Got it? Stay alert.

452
00:32:25,840 --> 00:32:27,360
The weather's dry now.

453
00:32:27,360 --> 00:32:29,160
Make sure to watch for fire tonight.

454
00:32:29,160 --> 00:32:30,000
Right.

455
00:32:42,360 --> 00:32:44,040
Who is the leader

456
00:32:45,080 --> 00:32:45,920
who just went by?

457
00:32:46,500 --> 00:32:47,959
The director of our Material Bureau.

458
00:32:58,720 --> 00:33:00,680
Can you pay me after today's work?

459
00:33:02,200 --> 00:33:03,280
Didn't I already tell you?

460
00:33:03,659 --> 00:33:04,752
Wait until the month's end.

461
00:33:05,000 --> 00:33:05,840
Get back to work.

462
00:33:05,960 --> 00:33:06,800
I quit.

463
00:33:07,439 --> 00:33:08,880
You've only been here for two days.

464
00:33:09,280 --> 00:33:10,200
Why quit?

465
00:33:11,720 --> 00:33:12,880
I'm not cut out for this.

466
00:33:19,960 --> 00:33:21,120
Faster.

467
00:33:22,560 --> 00:33:23,720
Give me your hand.

468
00:33:23,720 --> 00:33:26,020
(Promote physical culture;
Improve the people's health)

469
00:33:26,350 --> 00:33:27,460
Hold on to me.

470
00:33:30,630 --> 00:33:31,710
Everyone, follow me.

471
00:33:32,600 --> 00:33:33,440
Be careful.

472
00:33:38,060 --> 00:33:42,060
(Photo Studio)

473
00:33:51,280 --> 00:33:52,160
Sorry.

474
00:33:52,160 --> 00:33:53,126
Shiwu.

475
00:33:53,137 --> 00:33:54,120
It's hard to take photos.

476
00:33:54,120 --> 00:33:55,770
- Shiwu, we're done.
- Don't cry, okay?

477
00:33:55,960 --> 00:33:57,320
Listen to me.

478
00:33:57,320 --> 00:34:00,000
Smile at the camera for photos.

479
00:34:00,000 --> 00:34:00,840
Got it?

480
00:34:01,200 --> 00:34:02,080
No more tears, okay?

481
00:34:02,080 --> 00:34:03,080
The photo is done.

482
00:34:04,200 --> 00:34:06,360
You have to smile for photos.

483
00:34:07,440 --> 00:34:08,640
All right, all right.

484
00:35:34,000 --> 00:35:35,720
Mom, if you won't let me win,

485
00:35:35,720 --> 00:35:37,560
I can't go defend the realm.

486
00:35:37,880 --> 00:35:39,680
Go easy on me, and I'll get through.

487
00:35:41,320 --> 00:35:42,160
Oh, my.

488
00:35:42,280 --> 00:35:44,640
How could I ever beat you, Mom?

489
00:35:44,640 --> 00:35:46,080
- I'll go line up.
- Okay, okay.

490
00:35:46,080 --> 00:35:47,419
- Get the bowls.
- I'll get them.

491
00:36:09,640 --> 00:36:11,000
I need to tell you something.

492
00:36:11,880 --> 00:36:12,800
What is it?

493
00:36:13,840 --> 00:36:15,720
Are you with Feng Xiaoxiao now?

494
00:36:16,960 --> 00:36:18,200
You can't be with him.

495
00:36:19,320 --> 00:36:20,840
Because he and I got together ages ago.

496
00:36:22,480 --> 00:36:23,880
I won't fight you for Mu Guiying.

497
00:36:24,280 --> 00:36:26,080
But Feng Xiaoxiao is not up for grabs.

498
00:36:28,080 --> 00:36:29,520
Even if you try, I won't give him up.

499
00:36:30,840 --> 00:36:31,680
Yi Qing'e.

500
00:36:33,400 --> 00:36:34,240
Yi Qing'e.

501
00:36:35,320 --> 00:36:36,160
Yi Qing'e.

502
00:36:40,120 --> 00:36:41,080
What are you doing here?

503
00:36:41,760 --> 00:36:43,146
Why are you looking for Yi Qing'e?

504
00:36:44,320 --> 00:36:45,400
What's it to you?

505
00:36:51,760 --> 00:36:52,860
What were you talking about?

506
00:36:54,080 --> 00:36:55,480
Wait. What were you two saying?

507
00:36:58,480 --> 00:36:59,440
What are you two up to?

508
00:37:00,120 --> 00:37:01,080
What do you need?

509
00:37:03,200 --> 00:37:04,880
Master Gou wants us at the gatehouse.

510
00:37:06,560 --> 00:37:07,400
The two of us?

511
00:37:13,400 --> 00:37:14,240
Tell me.

512
00:37:15,320 --> 00:37:16,960
How were Yang Wenguang and Mu Guiying?

513
00:37:18,760 --> 00:37:19,840
I think it's pretty good.

514
00:37:25,080 --> 00:37:25,920
You tell me.

515
00:37:28,400 --> 00:37:29,240
I don't know.

516
00:37:29,880 --> 00:37:30,800
Not great.

517
00:37:31,200 --> 00:37:33,320
Why won't you look at Yang Wenguang?

518
00:37:33,880 --> 00:37:34,760
Why is that?

519
00:37:35,280 --> 00:37:36,120
Say it.

520
00:37:36,400 --> 00:37:37,560
Tell me why you won't look.

521
00:37:38,960 --> 00:37:40,560
I feel embarrassed.

522
00:37:41,120 --> 00:37:42,000
Embarrassed?

523
00:37:42,560 --> 00:37:44,040
You made that little spark

524
00:37:44,040 --> 00:37:45,600
completely flat.

525
00:37:47,000 --> 00:37:49,200
What matters for actors onstage?

526
00:37:49,720 --> 00:37:51,440
The actors' eyes.

527
00:37:52,040 --> 00:37:53,400
You haven't even trained your eyes.

528
00:37:53,400 --> 00:37:55,000
How can you perform opera?

529
00:37:57,080 --> 00:37:57,920
Go.

530
00:37:58,000 --> 00:37:59,040
Find a crowded place.

531
00:37:59,400 --> 00:38:00,720
Stare into Yang Wenguang's eyes.

532
00:38:00,913 --> 00:38:01,999
Don't let your mind wander.

533
00:38:02,320 --> 00:38:03,413
Practice it a hundred times.

534
00:38:03,760 --> 00:38:05,480
If that fails, do it a thousand.

535
00:38:05,480 --> 00:38:07,160
If that fails, do it ten thousand.

536
00:38:08,480 --> 00:38:09,320
What's so funny?

537
00:38:09,920 --> 00:38:10,800
You two, get out.

538
00:38:17,520 --> 00:38:18,360
Why are you

539
00:38:18,560 --> 00:38:19,720
embarrassed?

540
00:38:20,040 --> 00:38:20,880
No reason.

541
00:38:23,560 --> 00:38:24,880
Where should we practice then?

542
00:38:25,840 --> 00:38:27,560
On the dirt mound behind the kitchen.

543
00:38:28,160 --> 00:38:29,200
Master Gou said

544
00:38:29,200 --> 00:38:30,490
to find a crowded place.

545
00:38:30,490 --> 00:38:31,480
You eat first.

546
00:38:31,491 --> 00:38:33,191
We'll practice
at the dorm entrance after.

547
00:38:33,560 --> 00:38:34,440
I'm not going.

548
00:38:34,440 --> 00:38:35,960
If you won't, I'll go find Master Gou.

549
00:38:49,200 --> 00:38:50,120
Stay focused.

550
00:38:51,866 --> 00:38:53,090
- Look at me.
- Feng Xiaoxiao.

551
00:38:53,090 --> 00:38:54,280
Your eyes wandered off.

552
00:38:54,280 --> 00:38:55,920
Lie on the ground; then she'll see you.

553
00:38:57,200 --> 00:38:58,040
What's so funny?

554
00:38:59,240 --> 00:39:00,426
Go back if you want to laugh.

555
00:39:00,760 --> 00:39:02,080
Why did I ask you all here?

556
00:39:03,280 --> 00:39:04,120
Ignore them, okay?

557
00:39:05,200 --> 00:39:06,280
Focus on me. Look at me.

558
00:39:13,800 --> 00:39:14,640
Laughing?

559
00:39:15,720 --> 00:39:17,000
Laugh again, and I'll hit you.

560
00:39:19,320 --> 00:39:20,240
Ignore them, okay?

561
00:39:26,960 --> 00:39:28,166
Your eyes wandered off again.

562
